* Iron Raptor noticed that Prowl's eyes had lingered on her body for a second and then looked down at herself, was there mud on her somewhere or something?!
She looked on her arms and legs, she swung her tail around to look at it and checked on her back, was there?
After finding no mud or anything else on her body she then looked ahead again, well maybe he just looked at her for something to look at...or something like that.
Iron Raptor looked around her and saw that the forest seemed to become darker, she growled and kept a close eye out for anything that seemed unnatural. One never could tell when an ambush was to be sprung!
She looked at Prowl to see if she could tell his reactions to the surroundings by his body language, it was then that she saw his muscles moving beneath his plumage. Apparently by the tone of them and their bulk he either worked out or the constant Pred and Alliance battles kept him fit, either conclusion would work but she was impressed...also the fact that he could even carry a being the size of her.
Iron Raptor smiled at the comment he had made when they had first landed, that also triggered the comment that he had made to her when she had first been introduced to the Beast Wars. In simple words, when she had fell on him by cause of Rampage.
She shook her head as she followed him deeper into the forest, he was a piece of work!
Iron Raptor then regarded his skills, obviously he had been in the Beast Wars longer then she had been and was known for his skills.
Why didn't Liono decide to make him some marked rank, like second or even third...before she joined?
The answer eluded her but she knew that he was a very good soldier and obviously was very skillful.
She nodded and sighed as she followed Prowl, hearing his words. She always did like the sound of his voice, for some reason or another.*

" Yes, I guess so."
